definition.value: An alkyl substituent attached to the remainder of a molecule via oxygen.
Acyclic branched or unbranched hydrocarbons having a carbon-carbon triple bond and the general formula CnH2n-2, RC#CR.
A hexadecatrienoic acid having Z double bonds at positions 7, 10 and 13.
A monocarboxylic acid that is the 4',5-dihydroxylated metabolite of diclofenac.
An organochlorine compound that is a metabolite of diclofenac having hydroxy and methoxy groups at positions 3' and 4' respectively..
